This paper is about reinforcement learning (RL) algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper specifically focuses on deep RL algorithms, which are a subset of RL algorithms that use neural networks to approximate Q-values. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary sub-category for papers on RL algorithms. 

The paper also proposes a new algorithm that improves exploration in RL, which is a common topic in the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics), as RL algorithms are often used in robotics applications. 

The paper also presents a theoretical analysis of the proposed algorithm, which is related to the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper uses empirical evaluations to compare the proposed algorithm to existing methods, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
